description:
Now, we move on to uncover the life of John Calvin. Born in Nyon, near Paris in France, John had a happy start to life. As he grew up, he wanted to become a priest, but went on to study law to appease his father. Despite his own original intentions and his parents' wishes, his life took twists and turns, before his conversion set his destiny on course, becoming a great reformer. 

To learn more about John Calvin visit our website to read our extended article about his life.
